          "description": "Arrived at 11am on a Sunday and was seen in triage immediately (literally spent zero time in waiting room) and then was seen within 30 minutes by a doctor. Overall the medical staff was excellent and well-informed. I was given pain meds + sent to imaging within the first 4 hours or so.\n\nOnly downsides overall were how crowded the central ER area was (sorta felt like sardines) and the wait time after the imaging - even though I was was told I was going to be admitted/brought upstairs by 5pm, no beds were available until 4am so I had to stay overnight in the ER.",
