          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUjlAdM3qoeee5V9D-qrHF0yXRbTogcjDaLQyEK02QDoImTb1uwvg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "Most of the Emergency Room staff, nurses, and doctors were all very kind, knowledgeable, and very quick to see us get things moving. We only had one nurse who seemes like she was maybe burnt out and wore earbuds blaring music when dealing with us, which was not great. The emergency room was okay on cleanliness. My spouse was sent to the ER by his doctor and was admitted after 2hours, however, we spent 31hours in the ER waiting to go upstairs, this was the worst part. The ER staff and upstairs staff do not communicate or work together, which makes the admission process extremely long and awful.",
