        {
          "username": "Tatyana Miranda",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "103591107228951012041",
          "user_review_count": 2,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIz2uyDgZ0gloCryS0pdqy3zbU8KzFQKDIjEhPrSK5f3yc2V9Mn=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "I visited the ER at Mount Sinai for severe pelvic pain during pregnancy and was there from approximately 6:30 PM to 1 AM. I was told a physician would return to explain my imaging results, but instead I was handed discharge paperwork without any explanation. I ultimately had to request to speak with the doctor and was made to walk across the ER in severe pain to find her myself. While struggling to walk, I was repeatedly rushed by staff despite explaining my pain level.\n\nWhen I finally spoke with the physician, I felt dismissed and spoken to with irritation for asking questions about my results and treatment options. I was told my pain was \u201cnormal\u201d and that \u201cnothing was wrong,\u201d despite having significant difficulty walking. I left feeling unheard, unsupported, and without clear guidance regarding my condition.\n\nPatients deserve compassionate communication and respectful care, especially during pregnancy and while in severe pain.\n\nAllison Sauder MD should not be made attending overnight.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25ORk4wVTNPV3RXUW5CS1QzcEhibGRGVlZaalpFRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xcf483c70930b7945!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOnNFN0U3OWtWQnBKT3pHbldFVVZjZEE%7C%7C?hl=en",
